description:
&lt;p&gt;Locala Community Adult Therapy Service provides comprehensive care for adults in community settings. An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced Occupational therapist to join our Integrated Community Care Team. The Team works with people with a range of conditions providing urgent response for palliative patients and rehabilitation /equipment for patients with complex disabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role sits within the integrated community care team, working closely with the community nurses, physiotherapy and assistant practitioner colleagues. You will also be supported by the wider specialist Adult Community Therapy Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Colleagues need to be flexible in terms of service needs and there is an expectation that you are able to travel Kirklees wide. However, this post is based in the south of Kirklees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service provides high quality care to people in their own homes, community rehabilitation facilities and care homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires a motivated and dynamic person to work within this established service and it is essential that you have experience in working as part of a multidisciplinary team. Experience of treating people with complex disability, end of life and experience of working in a rehabilitation setting are also essential requirements of this post. Good communication skills and flexibility are essential qualities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are able to use your own initiative, be flexible in your approach, and are motivated to be part of a developing service, come and join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Locala is committed to helping employees achieve a positive work- life balance and promotes mobile and flexible working. Staff are provided with mobile technology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is subject to a Disclosure &amp; Barring Service (DBS) check and you must be able to fulfil the travel requirements of the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A comprehensive induction&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexible working opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supervision&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Annual appraisal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunities to attend internal training, external training identified through the&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;appraisal process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interdisciplinary working&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
